#: ../../../cmds/open.rst:15
msgid ""
"``open`` opens a file in its default application, using the appropriate tool "
"for the operating system. On GNU/Linux, this requires the common but "
"optional ``xdg-open`` utility, from the ``xdg-utils`` package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/open.rst:17
msgid ""
"Note that this function will not be used if a command by this name exists "
"(which is the case on macOS or Haiku)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/open.rst:21
msgid "Example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/open.rst:23
msgid ""
"``open *.txt`` opens all the text files in the current directory using your "
"system's default text editor."
msgstr ""
